==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[yarndi]]
*[[nyandi]]
===Etymology===
From Wiradhuri ''[[nyaandi]]'' "thingamajig, what's-its-name".
===Noun===
'''yarndie'''

# ''(Australian Aboriginal)'' [[marijuana]]
===Quotations===
*'''1984,''' L. Fogarty, ''Ngutji''
*:'''Yarndi''' = grass.
*'''1990,''' Davis et al., ''Paperbark''
*:He made enough to ... keep himself in '''Nyandi''' (herb).
*'''1992,''' ''Today,'' Sept.
*:It’s just as well it doesn’t depend on our feelings. Good feelings just fade like '''Yarndi''' smoke.
*'''1992,''' R. L. Ginibi, ''Real Deadly''
*:Ya can’t work had, drink, and some '''yarndie''' too!
*'''1993,''' ''Koori Mail,'' 10 Mar.
*:I drank and smoked '''yarndie''' for fourteen years.
